00:39:13.130 --> 00:39:14.430
&gt;&gt; David J. Bailey:
You know, there's,

00:39:14.430 --> 00:39:17.690
there are several studies
that show that families

00:39:17.690 --> 00:39:22.210
who were originally
middle class in terms

00:39:22.210 --> 00:39:27.050
of socioeconomic status, but
through some traumatic event,

00:39:27.050 --> 00:39:33.780
they are in poverty that, the
income has dropped so much,

00:39:33.780 --> 00:39:35.230
and they live in poverty.

00:39:35.230 --> 00:39:39.460
And even if they are able
to lift themselves up out

00:39:39.460 --> 00:39:43.120
of poverty after 15
months, the one year spent

00:39:43.120 --> 00:39:51.550
in poverty leads to, on average,
a delay in reading level that,

00:39:51.550 --> 00:39:57.260
for a slight majority of those
children, they don't catch up,

00:39:57.260 --> 00:40:01.520
even though the family is now
back into middle-class status.

00:40:01.520 --> 00:40:03.940
And I don't know
if they don't catch

00:40:03.940 --> 00:40:06.400
up because there's no
added intervention.

00:40:06.400 --> 00:40:08.040
It's not recognized.

00:40:08.040 --> 00:40:14.150
But relatively brief, if you can
call a year in poverty brief,

00:40:14.150 --> 00:40:16.350
adverse circumstances, traumas

00:40:16.350 --> 00:40:21.130
like that can have a
significant effect on literacy.

00:40:21.130 --> 00:40:26.090
And so as a society and as
Robert mentioned, you know,

00:40:26.090 --> 00:40:30.690
if a pediatric practice is
the primary medical home

00:40:30.690 --> 00:40:34.810
for that child, the physician,
the caregiver, those people

00:40:34.810 --> 00:40:38.010
in the office know
and understand

00:40:38.010 --> 00:40:41.660
when those traumatic occurrences
happen and can then begin

00:40:41.660 --> 00:40:48.080
to alert the family as to what
resources they may be able

00:40:48.080 --> 00:40:52.410
to avail themselves in the
community in order to, you know,

00:40:52.410 --> 00:40:56.230
prevent that reading
level being stunted

00:40:56.230 --> 00:40:59.090
